    "content": {
      "rendered": "<h2><span style=\"color: #993300;\"><strong>Updated:</strong></span> <a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2018/12/03/2019-cause-awareness-giving-day-calendar-for-nonprofits/\"><strong>2019 Cause Awareness &amp; Giving Day Calendar</strong></a></h2>\n<hr />\n<p>As a follow-up to <strong><a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2014/12/16/how-to-tap-into-the-power-of-cause-awareness-days/\">HOW TO: Tap Into the Power of Cause Awareness Days</a></strong>, below is a list of the most relevant international cause awareness days to the nonprofit sector. Cause awareness days can be powerful for fundraising because social network communities are highly likely\u00a0to promoting your nonprofit on cause awareness days provided that your nonprofit prepares in advance. The trick is to build a sense of anticipation among your followers and an essential first step is to select and add relevant cause awareness days to your nonprofit&#8217;s <strong><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=0AklDdlJTO1zxdGVIN0MtZEFMdDZ4amkzRDhZQ2hwdFE&amp;usp=sharing#gid=0\">editorial calendar</a></strong>.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>January</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>19:</strong> <a href=\"http://mlkday.gov/\">Martin Luther King, Jr. Day of Service</a><strong>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0</strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23MLKDay&amp;src=typd\">#MLKDay</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>February</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>2:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.ramsar.org/activity/world-wetlands-day-2015\">World Wetlands Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldWetlandsDay&amp;src=typd\">#WorldWetlandsDay</a><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Cancer_Day\"><br />\n</a> <strong>4:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.worldcancerday.org/\">World Cancer Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldCancerDay\">#WorldCancerDay</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldCancerDay\"><br />\n</a><strong>14:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.vday.org\">V-Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%231billionrising\">#1BillionRising<br />\n</a><strong>14:</strong> <a href=\"https://www.daysoftheyear.com/days/world-whale-day/\">World Whale Day</a> &#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldWhaleDay\">#WorldWhaleDay</a><br />\n<strong>20:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.un.org/en/events/socialjusticeday/\">World Day of Social Justice</a><strong>\u00a0&#8212;</strong>\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23SocialJusticeDay\">#SocialJusticeDay<br />\n</a><strong>24:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.worldspayday.org/\">World Spay Day</a><strong>\u00a0</strong>&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldSpayDay\">#WorldSpayDay<br />\n</a><strong>27:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.worldngoday.com/\">World NGO Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;<strong>\u00a0</strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldNGODay\">#WorldNGODay</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23SocialJusticeDay\"><br />\n</a><strong>28: </strong><a href=\"http://www.rarediseaseday.org/\">Rare Disease Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;<strong>\u00a0</strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23RareDiseaseDay\">#RareDiseaseDay</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>March</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>3: </strong><a href=\"http://wildlifeday.org/\">World Wildlife Day</a> &#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldWildlifeDay\">#WorldWildlifeDay</a><strong><br />\n8:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.internationalwomensday.com/theme.asp#.VI8DUyvF9gk\">International Women&#8217;s Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;<strong>\u00a0</strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23MakeItHappen\">#MakeItHappen</a> and\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23WomensDay\">#WomensDay</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23IWD2015\"><br />\n</a><strong>13:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.digitallearningday.org/\">Digital Learning Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23DLDay\">#DLDay</a><br />\n<strong>13:</strong>\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.worldkidneyday.org/\">World Kidney\u00a0Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;<strong>\u00a0</strong>#<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23worldkidneyday\">WorldKidneyDay<br />\n</a><strong>21: </strong><a href=\"http://www.un.org/en/events/racialdiscriminationday/\">International Day for the Elimination of Racial Discrimination</a> &#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23EndRacism\">#EndRacism</a><strong><br />\n</strong><strong style=\"font-size: 13px;\">22:</strong><a style=\"font-size: 13px;\" href=\"http://www.greeningtheblue.org/event/world-water-day-22nd-march-2011-0\">World Water Day</a><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\">\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0</span><a style=\"font-size: 13px;\" href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldWaterDay&amp;src=typd\">#WorldWaterDay<br />\n</a><strong>24:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.stoptb.org/events/world_tb_day/\">World Tuberculosis Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23WorldTBDay&amp;src=typd\">#WorldTBDay<br />\n</a><strong>28:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.earthhour.org/\">Earth Hour</a> &#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23EarthHour\">#EarthHour</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>April</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>2:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.autismspeaks.org/what-autism/world-autism-awareness-day\">World Autism Awareness Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23WorldAutismDay&amp;src=typd\">#WorldAustismDay</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23liub\">#LIUB</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23WorldAutismDay&amp;src=typd\"><br />\n</a><strong>12:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.streetchildrenday.org/\">International Day for Street Children</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23StreetChildrenDay\">#StreetChildrenDay</a><a href=\"http://www.streetchildrenday.org/\"><br />\n</a><strong>22:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.earthday.org/\">Earth Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23EarthDay&amp;src=typd\">#EarthDay<br />\n</a><strong>25:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.worldmalariaday.org\">World Malaria Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldMalariaDay\">#WorldMalariaDay<br />\n</a><strong>25: </strong><a href=\"http://www.greenpeace.org/international/en/getinvolved/Celebrate-World-Penguin-Day-by-protecting-their-homes/\">World Penguin Day</a> &#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldPenguinDay\">#WorldPenguinDay </a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>May</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>1:</strong> <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Workers'_Day\">International Workers&#8217; Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23LaborDay\">#LaborDay</a>\u00a0and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?f=realtime&amp;q=%23LabourDay\">#LabourDay<br />\n</a><strong>3:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.un.org/en/events/pressfreedomday/\">World Press Freedom Day</a> &#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldPressFreedomDay\">#WorldPressFreedomDay</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?f=realtime&amp;q=%23LabourDay\"><br />\n</a><strong>5:\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.givelocalamerica.org/\">Give Local America Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/GiveLocal15\">#GiveLocal15</a></strong><a href=\"http://www.fairtraderesource.org/wftd/\"><br />\n</a><strong>9:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.wfto.com/events/world-fair-trade-day\">World Fair Trade Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23FairTradeDay\">#WorldFairTradeDay<br />\n</a><strong>10:</strong>\u00a0<a href=\"http://worldlupusday.org/\">World Lupus Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldLupusDay\">#WorldLupusDay</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23IntDayOfFamilies\"><br />\n</a><strong>15:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.bikeleague.org/content/bike-month-dates-events-0\">National Bike to Work Day</a><strong>\u00a0</strong>&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23BikeToWorkDay\">#BikeToWorkDay<br />\n</a><strong>17:</strong> <a href=\"http://dayagainsthomophobia.org/buzz-worthy/idahot-2014-mobilisations-confirming-may-17-as-biggest-annual-lgbti-mobilisation-moment/\">International Day Against Homophpobia, Transphobia, and Biphobia</a> &#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23IDAHOT\">#IDAHOT</a><br />\n<strong>18:</strong> <a href=\"http://network.icom.museum/international-museum-day\">International Museum Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23museumday\">#MuseumDay</a><a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/WorldTurtleDay\"><br />\n</a> <strong>23:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/WorldTurtleDay\">World Turtle Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;<strong>\u00a0</strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23WorldTurtleDay&amp;src=typd\">#WorldTurtleDay<br />\n</a><strong>31:</strong>\u00a0<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_No_Tobacco_Day\">World No Tobacco Day</a><strong>\u00a0</strong>&#8212;<strong>\u00a0</strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldNoTobaccoDay\">#WorldNoTobaccoDay</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23WorldTurtleDay&amp;src=typd\"><br />\n</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>June</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>5: </strong><a href=\"http://www.unep.org/wed/\">World Environment Day</a> &#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldEnvironmentDay\">#WorldEnvironmentDay</a><strong><br />\n8:</strong> <a href=\"http://worldoceansday.org/\">World Oceans Day</a><strong>\u00a0</strong>&#8212;<strong>\u00a0</strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldOceansDay\">#WorldOceansDay</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldOceansDay\"><br />\n</a><strong>14:</strong> <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Blood_Donor_Day\">World Blood Donor Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23WorldBloodDonorDay\">#WorldBloodDonorDay</a><br />\n<strong>20:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.un.org/en/events/refugeeday/\">World Refugee Day</a><strong>\u00a0&#8212;</strong>\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23WorldRefugeeDay\">#WorldRefugeeDay</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>July</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>11:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.un.org/en/events/populationday/\">WorldPopulationDay</a><strong>\u00a0</strong>&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23WorldPopulationDay\">#WorldPopulationDay<br />\n</a><strong>18:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.mandeladay.com/\">Nelson Mandela International Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23MandelaDay\">#MandelaDay</a><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Tiger_Day\"><br />\n</a> <strong>29:</strong> <a href=\"http://tigerday.org/\">International Tiger Day</a><strong>\u00a0</strong>&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23TigerDay\">#TigerDay</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>August</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>9:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.un.org/en/events/indigenousday/\">International Day of the World&#8217;s Indigenous Peoples</a><strong>\u00a0</strong>&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23IndigenousDay\">#IndigenousDay<br />\n</a><strong>12:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.un.org/en/events/youthday/\">International Youth Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23youthday\">#YouthDay</a><a href=\"http://www.un.org/en/events/indigenousday/\"><br />\n</a><strong>12:</strong> <a href=\"http://worldelephantday.org/\">World Elephant Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldElephantDay\">#WorldElephantDay<br />\n</a><strong>19:</strong> <a href=\"http://worldhumanitarianday.org/\">World Humanitarian Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldHumanitarianDay\">#WorldHumanitarianDay</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>September</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>8:</strong> <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Literacy_Day\">International Literacy Day</a><strong>\u00a0</strong>&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23LiteracyDay\">#LiteracyDay<br />\n</a><strong>10:</strong>\u00a0<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Suicide_Prevention_Day\">World Suicide Prevention Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WSPD15\">#WSPD15<br />\n</a><strong>15:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.un.org/en/events/democracyday/\">International Day of Democracy</a> &#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23DemocracyDay\">#DemocracyDay</a><a href=\"http://www.internationaldayofpeace.org/\"><br />\n</a><strong>21:</strong> <a href=\"http://internationaldayofpeace.org/\">International Day of Peace</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23PeaceDay\">#PeaceDay</a><a href=\"http://www.worldrhinoday.org/\"><br />\n</a> <strong>22:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.worldrhinoday.org/\">World Rhino Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23WorldRhinoDay\">#WorldRhinoDay<br />\n</a><strong>27:</strong> <a href=\"http://worldriversday.com/\">World Rivers Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldRiversDay\">#WorldRiversDay</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>October</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>4:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.worldanimalday.co.uk/\">World Animal Day</a><strong>\u00a0</strong>&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23WorldAnimalDay\">#WorldAnimalDay<br />\n</a><strong>5:</strong> <a href=\"http://unhabitat.org/world-habitat-day/\">World Habitat Day</a> &#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldHabitatDay\">#WorldHabitatDay</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23WorldAnimalDay\"><br />\n</a><strong>5:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.5oct.org/\">World Teachers Day</a><strong>\u00a0</strong>&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23WorldTeachersDay\">#WorldTeachersDay</a><br />\n<strong>10:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.mentalhealth.org.uk/our-work/world-mental-health-day/\">World Mental Health Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;<strong>\u00a0</strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldMentalHealthDay\">#WorldMentalHealthDay<br />\n</a><strong>11:</strong> <a href=\"http://dayofthegirl.org/\">International Day of the Girl</a><strong>\u00a0</strong>&#8212;<b>\u00a0</b><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23DayOfTheGirl\">#DayOfTheGirl</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23NCOD\"><br />\n</a><strong>12:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.worldarthritisday.org/\">World Arthritis Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;<strong>\u00a0</strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23WorldArthritisDay\">#WorldArthritisDay<br />\n</a><strong>17:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.un.org/en/events/povertyday/\">International Day for the Eradication of Poverty</a> &#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23EndPovertyDay\">#EndPoveryDay</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>November</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>13: </strong><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Kindness_Day\">World Kindness Day</a> &#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldKindnessDay\">#WorldKindnessDay</a><strong><br />\n14:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.idf.org/worlddiabetesday/\">World Diabetes Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23WorldDiabetesDay\">#WorldDiabetesDay<br />\n</a><strong>16:</strong> <a href=\"http://globaldimension.org.uk/calendar/event/4585\">International Day for Tolerance</a> &#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23ToleranceDay\">#ToleranceDay</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23WorldDiabetesDay\"><br />\n</a><strong>20: </strong><a href=\"http://www.un.org/en/events/childrenday/\">Universal Children&#8217;s Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/realtime?q=%23ChildrensDay\">#ChildrensDay<br />\n</a><strong>25:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.un.org/en/events/endviolenceday/\">International Day for the Elimination of Violence Against Women</a> &#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23EndViolenceAgainstWomen\">#EndViolenceAgainstWomen</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>December</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>1: <a href=\"http://givingtuesday.org\">Giving Tuesday</a> &#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23GivingTuesday\">#GivingTuesday<br />\n</a>1: </strong><a href=\"http://www.worldaidsday.org/\">World AIDS Day</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23GivingTuesday\">\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23WorldAIDSDay&amp;src=typd\">#WorldAIDSDay</a><a href=\"http://www.worldaidsday.org/\"><br />\n</a><strong>3:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.idpwd.com.au/\">International Day of People with Disabilities</a>\u00a0&#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23IDPwD15\">#IDPwD15</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23IDPWD\"><br />\n</a><strong>5:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.volunteeractioncounts.org/en/\">International Volunteer Day</a> &#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23VolunteerDay\">#VolunteerDay</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23IVD2014\"><br />\n</a><strong>9:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.un.org/en/events/anticorruptionday/\">International Anti-Corruption Day </a>&#8212; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23AntiCorruptionDay\">#AntiCorruptionDay</a><a href=\"http://www.worldaidsday.org/\"><br />\n</a><strong>10:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.ohchr.org/EN/AboutUs/Pages/HumanRightsDay.aspx\">International Human Rights Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23HumanRightsDay\">#HumanRightsDay</a><br />\n<strong>11:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.un.org/en/events/mountainday/\">International Mountain Day</a>\u00a0&#8212;\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23mountainday\">#MountainDay</a></p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 17px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold;\"><em>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</em></span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-16024\" style=\"margin: 10px; border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/mobile-for-good-look-inside.jpg?resize=99%2C150\" alt=\"mobile for good look inside\" width=\"99\" height=\"150\" /></a>Based on more than 20 years of experience and 25,000+ hours spent utilizing mobile and social media, <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\"><em><strong>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</strong></em></a> is a comprehensive 256-page book packed with more than 500 best practices. Written on the premise that all communications and fundraising are now mobile and social, Mobile for Good is a step-by-step how-to guide for writing, implementing, and maintaining a mobile and social fundraising strategy for your nonprofit.</p>\n",
